23/10/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Meeting with Principal Deputy High Representative Raffi Gregorian on Monday (October 22nd) in Sarajevo, representatives of the World Congress of BiH Diaspora sought a more active role in the development of the country.
They say they could make an enormous contribution in terms of attracting investment and sharing knowledge gained from countries in which they now live.
The leader of the group, Senada Softic Telalovic, briefed Gregorian about forming a formal committee of the BiH Diaspora Council, under the auspices of the BiH Council of Ministers.
(OHR website, Fena, RTRS- 22/10/07)
